# Spring Boot Ultimate Production Rules - Transaction and Data Integrity (10 Rules)

1. Define transaction boundaries only in application/service layer methods.
2. Never open or manage transactions in controllers.
3. Use `@Transactional(readOnly = true)` for read paths.
4. Keep write transactions short and bounded; avoid network calls inside open transactions.
5. Use optimistic locking (`@Version`) for concurrent updates on mutable aggregates.
6. Enforce integrity with database constraints (PK, FK, unique, check), not only application code.
7. Use idempotency keys for externally retried write operations.
8. Apply transactional outbox for reliable event publication with database commits.
9. Avoid distributed XA transactions; prefer saga or compensating workflow patterns.
10. Declare rollback rules explicitly for checked exceptions where domain consistency requires it.
